[2026-03-13T17:46:46Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012GAyPX2yEq4qBfnMeAouk6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Рєњpackage main\n     2Рєњ\n     3Рєњimport (\n     4Рєњ\t\"context\"\n     5Рєњ\t\"encoding/json\"\n     6Рєњ\t\"errors\"\n     7Рєњ\t\"fmt\"\n     8Рєњ\t\"io\"\n     9Рєњ\t\"net/http\"\n    10Рєњ\t\"os\"\n    11Рєњ\t\"path/filepath\"\n    12Рєњ\t\"strings\"\n    13Рєњ\t\"time\"\n    14Рєњ\n    15Рєњ\tpb \"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb\"\n    16Рєњ\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    17Рєњ\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    18Рєњ\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/runcontext\"\n    19Рєњ\t\"google.golang.org/grpc\"\n    20Рєњ\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/credentials/insecure\"\n    21Рєњ\t\"google.golang.org/grpc/metadata\"\n    22Рєњ)\n    23Рєњ\n    24Рєњfunc main() {\n    25Рєњ\tif len(os.Args) < 2 {\n    26Рєњ\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n    27Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    28Рєњ\t}\n    29Рєњ\n    30Рєњ\t// Handle top-level help: \"cloche help\", \"cloche --help\", \"cloche -h\"\n    31Рєњ\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n    32Рєњ\tcase \"help\":\n    33Рєњ\t\tprintHelp(os.Args[2:])\n    34Рєњ\t\treturn\n    35Рєњ\tcase \"--help\", \"-h\":\n    36Рєњ\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n    37Рєњ\t\treturn\n    38Рєњ\t}\n    39Рєњ\n    40Рєњ\t// Commands that don't need a daemon connection\n    41Рєњ\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n    42Рєњ\tcase \"init\":\n    43Рєњ\t\tif hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    44Рєњ\t\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(\"init\")\n    45Рєњ\t\t\treturn\n    46Рєњ\t\t}\n    47Рєњ\t\tcmdInit(os.Args[2:])\n    48Рєњ\t\treturn\n    49Рєњ\tcase \"health\":\n    50Рєњ\t\tif hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    51Рєњ\t\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(\"health\")\n    52Рєњ\t\t\treturn\n    53Рєњ\t\t}\n    54Рєњ\t\tcmdHealth(os.Args[2:])\n    55Рєњ\t\treturn\n    56Рєњ\tcase \"get\":\n    57Рєњ\t\tif hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    58Рєњ\t\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(\"get\")\n    59Рєњ\t\t\treturn\n    60Рєњ\t\t}\n    61Рєњ\t\tcmdGet(os.Args[2:])\n    62Рєњ\t\treturn\n    63Рєњ\tcase \"set\":\n    64Рєњ\t\tif hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    65Рєњ\t\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(\"set\")\n    66Рєњ\t\t\treturn\n    67Рєњ\t\t}\n    68Рєњ\t\tcmdSet(os.Args[2:])\n    69Рєњ\t\treturn\n    70Рєњ\tcase \"tasks\":\n    71Рєњ\t\tif hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    72Рєњ\t\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(\"tasks\")\n    73Рєњ\t\t\treturn\n    74Рєњ\t\t}\n    75Рєњ\t\tcmdTasks(os.Args[2:])\n    76Рєњ\t\treturn\n    77Рєњ\t}\n    78Рєњ\n    79Рєњ\t// Handle --help for daemon commands before connecting\n    80Рєњ\tdaemonCmds := map[string]bool{\n    81Рєњ\t\t\"run\": true, \"status\": true, \"logs\": true, \"poll\": true,\n    82Рєњ\t\t\"list\": true, \"stop\": true, \"delete\": true, \"loop\": true, \"shutdown\": true,\n    83Рєњ\t}\n    84Рєњ\tif daemonCmds[os.Args[1]] && hasHelpFlag(os.Args[2:]) {\n    85Рєњ\t\tprintSubcommandHelp(os.Args[1])\n    86Рєњ\t\treturn\n    87Рєњ\t}\n    88Рєњ\n    89Рєњ\t// Commands that need a daemon connection\n    90Рєњ\taddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_ADDR\")\n    91Рєњ\tif addr == \"\" {\n    92Рєњ\t\taddr = \"unix:///tmp/cloche.sock\"\n    93Рєњ\t}\n    94Рєњ\n    95Рєњ\tconn, err := grpc.NewClient(addr, grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()))\n    96Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n    97Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"failed to connect: %v\\n\", err)\n    98Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n    99Рєњ\t}\n   100Рєњ\tdefer conn.Close()\n   101Рєњ\n   102Рєњ\tclient := pb.NewClocheServiceClient(conn)\n   103Рєњ\tctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), 30*time.Second)\n   104Рєњ\tdefer cancel()\n   105Рєњ\n   106Рєњ\tswitch os.Args[1] {\n   107Рєњ\tcase \"run\":\n   108Рєњ\t\tcmdRun(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   109Рєњ\tcase \"status\":\n   110Рєњ\t\tcmdStatus(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   111Рєњ\tcase \"logs\":\n   112Рєњ\t\tcmdLogs(client, os.Args[2:])\n   113Рєњ\tcase \"poll\":\n   114Рєњ\t\tcmdPoll(client, os.Args[2:])\n   115Рєњ\tcase \"list\":\n   116Рєњ\t\tcmdList(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   117Рєњ\tcase \"stop\":\n   118Рєњ\t\tcmdStop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   119Рєњ\tcase \"delete\":\n   120Рєњ\t\tcmdDelete(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   121Рєњ\tcase \"loop\":\n   122Рєњ\t\tcmdLoop(ctx, client, os.Args[2:])\n   123Рєњ\tcase \"shutdown\":\n   124Рєњ\t\tcmdShutdown(ctx, client)\n   125Рєњ\tdefault:\n   126Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", os.Args[1])\n   127Рєњ\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   128Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   129Рєњ\t}\n   130Рєњ}\n   131Рєњ\n   132Рєњ\n   133Рєњfunc cmdRun(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   134Рєњ\tvar workflow, prompt, title string\n   135Рєњ\tvar keepContainer bool\n   136Рєњ\n   137Рєњ\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n   138Рєњ\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   139Рєњ\t\tcase \"--workflow\":\n   140Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   141Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   142Рєњ\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   143Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   144Рєњ\t\tcase \"--prompt\", \"-p\":\n   145Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   146Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   147Рєњ\t\t\t\tprompt = args[i]\n   148Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   149Рєњ\t\tcase \"--title\":\n   150Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   151Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   152Рєњ\t\t\t\ttitle = args[i]\n   153Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   154Рєњ\t\tcase \"--keep-container\":\n   155Рєњ\t\t\tkeepContainer = true\n   156Рєњ\t\tdefault:\n   157Рєњ\t\t\t// Support bare positional arg as workflow name for backwards compat\n   158Рєњ\t\t\tif workflow == \"\" && !strings.HasPrefix(args[i], \"-\") {\n   159Рєњ\t\t\t\tworkflow = args[i]\n   160Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   161Рєњ\t\t}\n   162Рєњ\t}\n   163Рєњ\n   164Рєњ\tif workflow == \"\" {\n   165Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \\\"...\\\"] [--title \\\"...\\\"]\\n\")\n   166Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   167Рєњ\t}\n   168Рєњ\n   169Рєњ\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   170Рєњ\n   171Рєњ\t// Resolve image from workflow file (soft failure Рђћ fall back to daemon default)\n   172Рєњ\tvar image string\n   173Рєњ\twfPath := filepath.Join(cwd, \".cloche\", workflow+\".cloche\")\n   174Рєњ\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(wfPath); err == nil {\n   175Рєњ\t\tif wf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data)); err == nil {\n   176Рєњ\t\t\timage = wf.Config[\"container.image\"]\n   177Рєњ\t\t}\n   178Рєњ\t}\n   179Рєњ\n   180Рєњ\tresp, err := client.RunWorkflow(ctx, &pb.RunWorkflowRequest{\n   181Рєњ\t\tWorkflowName:  workflow,\n   182Рєњ\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n   183Рєњ\t\tImage:         image,\n   184Рєњ\t\tPrompt:        prompt,\n   185Рєњ\t\tKeepContainer: keepContainer,\n   186Рєњ\t\tTitle:         title,\n   187Рєњ\t})\n   188Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   189Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   190Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   191Рєњ\t}\n   192Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Started run: %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n   193Рєњ}\n   194Рєњ\n   195Рєњfunc cmdStatus(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   196Рєњ\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   197Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche status <run-id>\\n\")\n   198Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   199Рєњ\t}\n   200Рєњ\n   201Рєњ\tresp, err := client.GetStatus(ctx, &pb.GetStatusRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n   202Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   203Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   204Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   205Рєњ\t}\n   206Рєњ\n   207Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Run:       %s\\n\", resp.RunId)\n   208Рєњ\tif resp.Title != \"\" {\n   209Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Title:     %s\\n\", resp.Title)\n   210Рєњ\t}\n   211Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Workflow:  %s\\n\", resp.WorkflowName)\n   212Рєњ\tif resp.IsHost {\n   213Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      host\\n\")\n   214Рєњ\t} else {\n   215Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Type:      container\\n\")\n   216Рєњ\t}\n   217Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"State:     %s\\n\", resp.State)\n   218Рєњ\tif resp.ContainerId != \"\" {\n   219Рєњ\t\tcid := resp.ContainerId\n   220Рєњ\t\tif len(cid) > 12 {\n   221Рєњ\t\t\tcid = cid[:12]\n   222Рєњ\t\t}\n   223Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Container: %s\\n\", cid)\n   224Рєњ\t}\n   225Рєњ\tif resp.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n   226Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:     %s\\n\", resp.ErrorMessage)\n   227Рєњ\t}\n   228Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Active:    %s\\n\", resp.CurrentStep)\n   229Рєњ\tfor _, exec := range resp.StepExecutions {\n   230Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"  %s: %s (%s -> %s)\\n\", exec.StepName, exec.Result, exec.StartedAt, exec.CompletedAt)\n   231Рєњ\t}\n   232Рєњ}\n   233Рєњ\n   234Рєњfunc cmdList(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   235Рєњ\tvar all bool\n   236Рєњ\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   237Рєњ\t\tif arg == \"--all\" {\n   238Рєњ\t\t\tall = true\n   239Рєњ\t\t}\n   240Рєњ\t}\n   241Рєњ\n   242Рєњ\treq := &pb.ListRunsRequest{}\n   243Рєњ\tif all {\n   244Рєњ\t\t// --all: show all runs across all projects (no time limit)\n   245Рєњ\t\treq.All = true\n   246Рєњ\t} else {\n   247Рєњ\t\t// Default: filter to current project\n   248Рєњ\t\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   249Рєњ\t\treq.ProjectDir = cwd\n   250Рєњ\t}\n   251Рєњ\n   252Рєњ\tresp, err := client.ListRuns(ctx, req)\n   253Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   254Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   255Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   256Рєњ\t}\n   257Рєњ\n   258Рєњ\tif len(resp.Runs) == 0 {\n   259Рєњ\t\tfmt.Println(\"No runs found.\")\n   260Рєњ\t\treturn\n   261Рєњ\t}\n   262Рєњ\n   263Рєњ\tfor _, run := range resp.Runs {\n   264Рєњ\t\trunType := \"container\"\n   265Рєњ\t\tif run.IsHost {\n   266Рєњ\t\t\trunType = \"host\"\n   267Рєњ\t\t}\n   268Рєњ\t\tline := fmt.Sprintf(\"%s  %-20s  %-10s  %-9s\", run.RunId, run.WorkflowName, run.State, runType)\n   269Рєњ\t\tif run.Title != \"\" {\n   270Рєњ\t\t\tt := run.Title\n   271Рєњ\t\t\tif len(t) > 40 {\n   272Рєњ\t\t\t\tt = t[:37] + \"...\"\n   273Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   274Рєњ\t\t\tline += \"  \" + t\n   275Рєњ\t\t}\n   276Рєњ\t\tif run.ContainerId != \"\" {\n   277Рєњ\t\t\tline += \"  \" + run.ContainerId\n   278Рєњ\t\t}\n   279Рєњ\t\tif run.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n   280Рєњ\t\t\terrMsg := run.ErrorMessage\n   281Рєњ\t\t\tif len(errMsg) > 60 {\n   282Рєњ\t\t\t\terrMsg = errMsg[:57] + \"...\"\n   283Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   284Рєњ\t\t\tline += \"  \" + errMsg\n   285Рєњ\t\t}\n   286Рєњ\t\tfmt.Println(line)\n   287Рєњ\t}\n   288Рєњ}\n   289Рєњ\n   290Рєњfunc cmdLogs(client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   291Рєњ\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   292Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\\n\")\n   293Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   294Рєњ\t}\n   295Рєњ\n   296Рєњ\tvar stepFilter, typeFilter string\n   297Рєњ\tvar follow bool\n   298Рєњ\trunID := args[0]\n   299Рєњ\n   300Рєњ\tfor i := 1; i < len(args); i++ {\n   301Рєњ\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   302Рєњ\t\tcase \"--step\":\n   303Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   304Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   305Рєњ\t\t\t\tstepFilter = args[i]\n   306Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   307Рєњ\t\tcase \"--type\":\n   308Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   309Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   310Рєњ\t\t\t\ttypeFilter = args[i]\n   311Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   312Рєњ\t\tcase \"--follow\", \"-f\":\n   313Рєњ\t\t\tfollow = true\n   314Рєњ\t\t}\n   315Рєњ\t}\n   316Рєњ\n   317Рєњ\t// Use background context Рђћ log output can be large and follow mode blocks.\n   318Рєњ\tctx := context.Background()\n   319Рєњ\tif follow {\n   320Рєњ\t\tmd := metadata.Pairs(\"x-cloche-follow\", \"true\")\n   321Рєњ\t\tctx = metadata.NewOutgoingContext(ctx, md)\n   322Рєњ\t}\n   323Рєњ\n   324Рєњ\tstream, err := client.StreamLogs(ctx, &pb.StreamLogsRequest{\n   325Рєњ\t\tRunId:    runID,\n   326Рєњ\t\tStepName: stepFilter,\n   327Рєњ\t\tLogType:  typeFilter,\n   328Рєњ\t})\n   329Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   330Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   331Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   332Рєњ\t}\n   333Рєњ\n   334Рєњ\tfor {\n   335Рєњ\t\tentry, err := stream.Recv()\n   336Рєњ\t\tif err != nil {\n   337Рєњ\t\t\tif errors.Is(err, io.EOF) {\n   338Рєњ\t\t\t\tbreak\n   339Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   340Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error reading logs: %v\\n\", err)\n   341Рєњ\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   342Рєњ\t\t}\n   343Рєњ\n   344Рєњ\t\tswitch entry.Type {\n   345Рєњ\t\tcase \"step_started\":\n   346Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s started ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n   347Рєњ\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   348Рєњ\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   349Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   350Рєњ\t\tcase \"step_completed\":\n   351Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s: %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName, entry.Result)\n   352Рєњ\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   353Рєњ\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   354Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   355Рєњ\t\tcase \"run_completed\":\n   356Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"\\nRun result: %s\\n\", entry.Result)\n   357Рєњ\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   358Рєњ\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Error:      %s\\n\", entry.Message)\n   359Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   360Рєњ\t\tcase \"full_log\":\n   361Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n   362Рєњ\t\tcase \"log\":\n   363Рєњ\t\t\t// Live-streamed log line from an active run.\n   364Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Println(entry.Message)\n   365Рєњ\t\tdefault:\n   366Рєњ\t\t\t// Handles filtered log entries like \"script_log\", \"llm_log\", \"step_log\"\n   367Рєњ\t\t\tif entry.StepName != \"\" {\n   368Рєњ\t\t\t\tfmt.Printf(\"--- %s ---\\n\", entry.StepName)\n   369Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   370Рєњ\t\t\tif entry.Message != \"\" {\n   371Рєњ\t\t\t\tfmt.Print(string(logstream.ParseClaudeStream([]byte(entry.Message))))\n   372Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   373Рєњ\t\t}\n   374Рєњ\t}\n   375Рєњ}\n   376Рєњ\n   377Рєњfunc cmdStop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   378Рєњ\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   379Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche stop <run-id>\\n\")\n   380Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   381Рєњ\t}\n   382Рєњ\n   383Рєњ\t_, err := client.StopRun(ctx, &pb.StopRunRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n   384Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   385Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   386Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   387Рєњ\t}\n   388Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Stopped run: %s\\n\", args[0])\n   389Рєњ}\n   390Рєњ\n   391Рєњfunc cmdDelete(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   392Рєњ\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   393Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\\n\")\n   394Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   395Рєњ\t}\n   396Рєњ\n   397Рєњ\t_, err := client.DeleteContainer(ctx, &pb.DeleteContainerRequest{Id: args[0]})\n   398Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   399Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   400Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   401Рєњ\t}\n   402Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"Deleted container: %s\\n\", args[0])\n   403Рєњ}\n   404Рєњ\n   405Рєњfunc cmdLoop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n   406Рєњ\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   407Рєњ\n   408Рєњ\t// Check for \"stop\" subcommand\n   409Рєњ\tif len(args) > 0 && args[0] == \"stop\" {\n   410Рєњ\t\t_, err := client.DisableLoop(ctx, &pb.DisableLoopRequest{ProjectDir: cwd})\n   411Рєњ\t\tif err != nil {\n   412Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   413Рєњ\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   414Рєњ\t\t}\n   415Рєњ\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop stopped.\")\n   416Рєњ\t\treturn\n   417Рєњ\t}\n   418Рєњ\n   419Рєњ\t// Default: 0 means \"use config value\" (server reads .cloche/config.toml).\n   420Рєњ\tvar maxConcurrent int32\n   421Рєњ\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n   422Рєњ\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   423Рєњ\t\tcase \"--max\":\n   424Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   425Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   426Рєњ\t\t\t\tn, err := fmt.Sscanf(args[i], \"%d\", &maxConcurrent)\n   427Рєњ\t\t\t\tif n != 1 || err != nil {\n   428Рєњ\t\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"invalid --max value: %s\\n\", args[i])\n   429Рєњ\t\t\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   430Рєњ\t\t\t\t}\n   431Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   432Рєњ\t\t}\n   433Рєњ\t}\n   434Рєњ\n   435Рєњ\t_, err := client.EnableLoop(ctx, &pb.EnableLoopRequest{\n   436Рєњ\t\tProjectDir:    cwd,\n   437Рєњ\t\tMaxConcurrent: maxConcurrent,\n   438Рєњ\t})\n   439Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   440Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   441Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   442Рєњ\t}\n   443Рєњ\tif maxConcurrent > 0 {\n   444Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"Orchestration loop started (max_concurrent=%d).\\n\", maxConcurrent)\n   445Рєњ\t} else {\n   446Рєњ\t\tfmt.Println(\"Orchestration loop started (using config defaults).\")\n   447Рєњ\t}\n   448Рєњ}\n   449Рєњ\n   450Рєњfunc cmdTasks(args []string) {\n   451Рєњ\t// Determine HTTP address from env\n   452Рєњ\thttpAddr := os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_HTTP\")\n   453Рєњ\tif httpAddr == \"\" {\n   454Рєњ\t\thttpAddr = \"localhost:8080\"\n   455Рєњ\t}\n   456Рєњ\thttpAddr = strings.TrimPrefix(httpAddr, \"http://\")\n   457Рєњ\n   458Рєњ\t// Determine project label from --project flag or current directory\n   459Рєњ\tprojectDir := \"\"\n   460Рєњ\tfor i := 0; i < len(args); i++ {\n   461Рєњ\t\tswitch args[i] {\n   462Рєњ\t\tcase \"--project\":\n   463Рєњ\t\t\tif i+1 < len(args) {\n   464Рєњ\t\t\t\ti++\n   465Рєњ\t\t\t\tprojectDir = args[i]\n   466Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   467Рєњ\t\t}\n   468Рєњ\t}\n   469Рєњ\n   470Рєњ\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   471Рєњ\t\tcwd, _ := os.Getwd()\n   472Рєњ\t\tprojectDir = filepath.Base(cwd)\n   473Рєњ\t}\n   474Рєњ\n   475Рєњ\ttasksURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s/api/projects/%s/tasks\", httpAddr, projectDir)\n   476Рєњ\tresp, err := http.Get(tasksURL)\n   477Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   478Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error connecting to daemon web API: %v\\n\", err)\n   479Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"hint: ensure CLOCHE_HTTP is set and the daemon is running with --http\\n\")\n   480Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   481Рєњ\t}\n   482Рєњ\tdefer resp.Body.Close()\n   483Рєњ\n   484Рєњ\tif resp.StatusCode != 200 {\n   485Рєњ\t\tbody, _ := io.ReadAll(resp.Body)\n   486Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: HTTP %d: %s\\n\", resp.StatusCode, strings.TrimSpace(string(body)))\n   487Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   488Рєњ\t}\n   489Рєњ\n   490Рєњ\ttype taskEntry struct {\n   491Рєњ\t\tID          string `json:\"id\"`\n   492Рєњ\t\tStatus      string `json:\"status\"`\n   493Рєњ\t\tTitle       string `json:\"title\"`\n   494Рєњ\t\tDescription string `json:\"description\"`\n   495Рєњ\t\tAssigned    bool   `json:\"assigned\"`\n   496Рєњ\t\tAssignedAt  string `json:\"assigned_at\"`\n   497Рєњ\t\tRunID       string `json:\"run_id\"`\n   498Рєњ\t}\n   499Рєњ\n   500Рєњ\tvar tasks []taskEntry\n   501Рєњ\tif err := json.NewDecoder(resp.Body).Decode(&tasks); err != nil {\n   502Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error parsing response: %v\\n\", err)\n   503Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   504Рєњ\t}\n   505Рєњ\n   506Рєњ\tif len(tasks) == 0 {\n   507Рєњ\t\tfmt.Println(\"No tasks found. (Is the orchestration loop running?)\")\n   508Рєњ\t\treturn\n   509Рєњ\t}\n   510Рєњ\n   511Рєњ\tfmt.Printf(\"%-20s  %-12s  %-10s  %-30s  %s\\n\", \"ID\", \"STATUS\", \"ASSIGNED\", \"RUN\", \"TITLE\")\n   512Рєњ\tfor _, t := range tasks {\n   513Рєњ\t\tstatus := t.Status\n   514Рєњ\t\tif status == \"\" {\n   515Рєњ\t\t\tstatus = \"open\"\n   516Рєњ\t\t}\n   517Рєњ\t\tassigned := \"-\"\n   518Рєњ\t\tif t.Assigned {\n   519Рєњ\t\t\tassigned = \"yes\"\n   520Рєњ\t\t}\n   521Рєњ\t\trunID := \"\"\n   522Рєњ\t\tif t.RunID != \"\" {\n   523Рєњ\t\t\trunID = t.RunID\n   524Рєњ\t\t\tif len(runID) > 30 {\n   525Рєњ\t\t\t\trunID = runID[:27] + \"...\"\n   526Рєњ\t\t\t}\n   527Рєњ\t\t}\n   528Рєњ\t\ttitle := t.Title\n   529Рєњ\t\tif len(title) > 40 {\n   530Рєњ\t\t\ttitle = title[:37] + \"...\"\n   531Рєњ\t\t}\n   532Рєњ\t\tfmt.Printf(\"%-20s  %-12s  %-10s  %-30s  %s\\n\", t.ID, status, assigned, runID, title)\n   533Рєњ\t}\n   534Рєњ}\n   535Рєњ\n   536Рєњfunc cmdShutdown(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient) {\n   537Рєњ\t_, err := client.Shutdown(ctx, &pb.ShutdownRequest{})\n   538Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   539Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   540Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   541Рєњ\t}\n   542Рєњ\tfmt.Println(\"Daemon shutting down.\")\n   543Рєњ}\n   544Рєњ\n   545Рєњ// resolveRunContext returns the project directory and run ID for context\n   546Рєњ// commands. The run ID comes from CLOCHE_RUN_ID and the project directory\n   547Рєњ// from CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR (falling back to cwd).\n   548Рєњfunc resolveRunContext() (projectDir, runID string, err error) {\n   549Рєњ\trunID = os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID\")\n   550Рєњ\tif runID == \"\" {\n   551Рєњ\t\treturn \"\", \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"CLOCHE_RUN_ID environment variable is not set\")\n   552Рєњ\t}\n   553Рєњ\tprojectDir = os.Getenv(\"CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR\")\n   554Рєњ\tif projectDir == \"\" {\n   555Рєњ\t\tprojectDir, err = os.Getwd()\n   556Рєњ\t\tif err != nil {\n   557Рєњ\t\t\treturn \"\", \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"getting working directory: %w\", err)\n   558Рєњ\t\t}\n   559Рєњ\t}\n   560Рєњ\treturn projectDir, runID, nil\n   561Рєњ}\n   562Рєњ\n   563Рєњfunc cmdGet(args []string) {\n   564Рєњ\tif len(args) < 1 {\n   565Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche get <key>\\n\")\n   566Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   567Рєњ\t}\n   568Рєњ\n   569Рєњ\tprojectDir, runID, err := resolveRunContext()\n   570Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   571Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   572Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   573Рєњ\t}\n   574Рєњ\n   575Рєњ\tval, ok, err := runcontext.Get(projectDir, runID, args[0])\n   576Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   577Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   578Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   579Рєњ\t}\n   580Рєњ\tif !ok {\n   581Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   582Рєњ\t}\n   583Рєњ\tfmt.Println(val)\n   584Рєњ}\n   585Рєњ\n   586Рєњfunc cmdSet(args []string) {\n   587Рєњ\tif len(args) < 2 {\n   588Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche set <key> <value>\\n\")\n   589Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"       cloche set <key> -     (read value from stdin)\\n\")\n   590Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   591Рєњ\t}\n   592Рєњ\n   593Рєњ\tprojectDir, runID, err := resolveRunContext()\n   594Рєњ\tif err != nil {\n   595Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   596Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   597Рєњ\t}\n   598Рєњ\n   599Рєњ\tvalue := args[1]\n   600Рєњ\tif value == \"-\" {\n   601Рєњ\t\tdata, err := io.ReadAll(os.Stdin)\n   602Рєњ\t\tif err != nil {\n   603Рєњ\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error reading stdin: %v\\n\", err)\n   604Рєњ\t\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   605Рєњ\t\t}\n   606Рєњ\t\tvalue = strings.TrimRight(string(data), \"\\n\")\n   607Рєњ\t}\n   608Рєњ\n   609Рєњ\tif err := runcontext.Set(projectDir, runID, args[0], value); err != nil {\n   610Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n   611Рєњ\t\tos.Exit(1)\n   612Рєњ\t}\n   613Рєњ}\n   614Рєњ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9B5ZLwaA81q4buXwXBtpB","session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"519a0d9b-1b7f-44fa-9238-35ef4c33fa5d"}
[2026-03-13T17:46:46Z] [llm] {"type":"system","subtype":"task_progress","task_id":"a5469156fb2965161","tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9B5ZLwaA81q4buXwXBtpB","description":"Reading docs/workflows.md","usage":{"total_tokens":15816,"tool_uses":4,"duration_ms":4321},"last_tool_name":"Read","uuid":"bbdd00c2-f705-45f4-b0d6-fb58644595a2","session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba"}
[2026-03-13T17:46:46Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01YULSAhF9A4kUmBqQjDgEnU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017jmUmaBZyDUc9X4oMh3gZK","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/workflows.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":4,"cache_creation_input_tokens":965,"cache_read_input_tokens":14832,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":965,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9B5ZLwaA81q4buXwXBtpB","session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"61d84d44-986a-4531-b4e8-9aa57431a1e1"}
[2026-03-13T17:46:46Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017jmUmaBZyDUc9X4oMh3gZK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Рєњ# Workflows\n     2Рєњ\n     3РєњCloche workflows define a directed graph of steps connected by named results.\n     4Рєњ\n     5Рєњ## Workflow Locations\n     6Рєњ\n     7РєњCloche distinguishes two workflow locations based on the file they live in:\n     8Рєњ\n     9Рєњ**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) Рђћ Run inside a Docker\n    10Рєњcontainer via `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type. These are the\n    11Рєњstandard workflows for coding tasks.\n    12Рєњ\n    13Рєњ**Host workflows** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) Рђћ Run on the host machine as the daemon\n    14Рєњprocess. Steps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow` step type\n    15Рєњdispatches a container workflow run and waits for it to complete. This is the extension\n    16Рєњpoint for custom orchestration strategies.\n    17Рєњ\n    18РєњA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n    19Рєњuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n    20Рєњ\n    21Рєњ| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n    22Рєњ|-------|--------------|---------|\n    23Рєњ| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n    24Рєњ| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n    25Рєњ| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n    26Рєњ\n    27РєњOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a legacy\n    28Рєњsingle-function mode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n    29Рєњ\n    30РєњThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n    31Рєњobject with the following fields:\n    32Рєњ\n    33Рєњ| Field | Required | Description |\n    34Рєњ|-------|----------|-------------|\n    35Рєњ| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n    36Рєњ| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n    37Рєњ| `title` | no | Short summary |\n    38Рєњ| `description` | no | Full description |\n    39Рєњ| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n    40Рєњ\n    41РєњThe daemon picks the first task with status `open` (or empty, for backward\n    42Рєњcompatibility), runs `main` with that task ID, then runs `finalize` with the outcome.\n    43РєњTasks are deduplicated within a configurable timeout window to prevent rapid\n    44Рєњreassignment.\n    45Рєњ\n    46РєњThe convention is enforced at parse time: a `workflow_name` step in a container workflow\n    47Рєњfile is a parse error.\n    48Рєњ\n    49Рєњ## Concepts\n    50Рєњ\n    51Рєњ| Concept  | Description                                                        |\n    52Рєњ|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n    53Рєњ| workflow | A named graph of steps connected by result wiring                  |\n    54Рєњ| step     | A unit of work (inferred: `prompt` = agent, `run` = script)        |\n    55Рєњ| result   | A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. \"success\", \"fail\")       |\n    56Рєњ| wiring   | Maps a step's result to the next step, with optional output mappings |\n    57Рєњ| done     | Built-in terminal step Рђћ successful completion                     |\n    58Рєњ| abort    | Built-in terminal step Рђћ failure with error reporting              |\n    59Рєњ\n    60Рєњ## Step Types\n    61Рєњ\n    62РєњStep type is inferred from the fields present in the step body:\n    63Рєњ\n    64Рєњ**agent** (has `prompt`) Рђћ Invokes a coding agent (Claude Code, or any tool conforming\n    65Рєњto the agent adapter interface) with a prompt. The agent works autonomously inside the\n    66Рєњcontainer. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    67Рєњ\n    68Рєњ**script** (has `run`) Рђћ Runs a shell command. Used for tests, linters, validators, or\n    69Рєњany deterministic check. Available in both host and container workflows.\n    70Рєњ\n    71Рєњ**workflow** (has `workflow_name`) Рђћ Dispatches a named container workflow run and blocks\n    72Рєњuntil it completes. Only available in host workflows (`host.cloche`).\n    73Рєњ\n    74РєњA step with more than one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`, or none of them, is a\n    75Рєњparse error.\n    76Рєњ\n    77Рєњ## DSL Syntax\n    78Рєњ\n    79Рєњ```\n    80Рєњworkflow \"develop\" {\n    81Рєњ  container {\n    82Рєњ    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n    83Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n    84Рєњ  }\n    85Рєњ\n    86Рєњ  step implement {\n    87Рєњ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    88Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n    89Рєњ  }\n    90Рєњ\n    91Рєњ  step test {\n    92Рєњ    run = \"make test && make lint\"\n    93Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n    94Рєњ  }\n    95Рєњ\n    96Рєњ  step fix {\n    97Рєњ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n    98Рєњ    max_attempts = \"3\"\n    99Рєњ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   100Рєњ  }\n   101Рєњ\n   102Рєњ  // Wiring: step:result -> next_step [optional output mappings]\n   103Рєњ  implement:success -> test\n   104Рєњ  implement:fail    -> abort\n   105Рєњ  test:success      -> done\n   106Рєњ  test:fail         -> fix\n   107Рєњ  fix:success       -> test\n   108Рєњ  fix:fail          -> abort\n   109Рєњ  fix:give-up       -> abort\n   110Рєњ}\n   111Рєњ```\n   112Рєњ\n   113Рєњ## Key Properties\n   114Рєњ\n   115Рєњ**Step type is inferred from content.** A `prompt` field makes it an agent step; a `run`\n   116Рєњfield makes it a script step.\n   117Рєњ\n   118Рєњ**Steps declare their possible results.** A step decides at runtime which result to\n   119Рєњreport. The graph engine follows the wiring to determine the next step.\n   120Рєњ\n   121Рєњ**Wiring is separate from step definitions.** This enables inserting new steps between\n   122Рєњexisting ones by rewiring Рђћ without modifying either step. This is the foundation for\n   123РєњCloche's self-evolution feature.\n   124Рєњ\n   125Рєњ**Graphs are validated at parse time.** The parser checks that all declared results are\n   126Рєњwired, no steps are orphaned, and an entry point exists.\n   127Рєњ\n   128Рєњ## Wire Output Mappings\n   129Рєњ\n   130РєњWires can include output mappings that extract values from a step's output and inject\n   131Рєњthem as environment variables into the target step:\n   132Рєњ\n   133Рєњ```\n   134Рєњstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135Рєњ```\n   136Рєњ\n   137РєњThe general form:\n   138Рєњ\n   139Рєњ```\n   140РєњFROM:RESULT -> TO [ KEY = EXPR, KEY = EXPR, ... ]\n   141Рєњ```\n   142Рєњ\n   143РєњWhere `KEY` is the environment variable name and `EXPR` is an output path expression\n   144Рєњstarting with the contextual keyword `output`:\n   145Рєњ\n   146Рєњ| Expression | Meaning |\n   147Рєњ|---|---|\n   148Рєњ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   149Рєњ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   150Рєњ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   151Рєњ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   152Рєњ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   153Рєњ\n   154РєњIf the source step's output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the parsed\n   155Рєњstructure. If the output is plain text, only bare `output` is valid. The resolved\n   156Рєњvalue is converted to a string for env var injection.\n   157Рєњ\n   158РєњIf two wires targeting the same step both map the same env var key, validation\n   159Рєњreturns an error (the mapping would be ambiguous). The same key may be used on\n   160Рєњwires to different steps without conflict.\n   161Рєњ\n   162Рєњ## Workflow-Level Configuration Blocks\n   163Рєњ\n   164РєњWorkflows support a configuration block at the workflow level to set defaults for all\n   165Рєњsteps. The block name depends on the workflow location:\n   166Рєњ\n   167Рєњ**`container {}`** Рђћ For container workflows. Sets container image, agent command, and\n   168Рєњnetwork allowlist.\n   169Рєњ\n   170Рєњ```\n   171Рєњworkflow \"develop\" {\n   172Рєњ  container {\n   173Рєњ    image = \"my-project:latest\"\n   174Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   175Рєњ    agent_args = \"-p --dangerously-skip-permissions\"\n   176Рєњ  }\n   177Рєњ  ...\n   178Рєњ}\n   179Рєњ```\n   180Рєњ\n   181РєњSupported keys: `image`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`, `network_allow`.\n   182Рєњ\n   183Рєњ**`host {}`** Рђћ For host workflows (`host.cloche`). Sets agent defaults for agent steps\n   184Рєњrunning on the host machine.\n   185Рєњ\n   186Рєњ```\n   187Рєњworkflow \"main\" {\n   188Рєњ  host {\n   189Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   190Рєњ  }\n   191Рєњ  ...\n   192Рєњ}\n   193Рєњ```\n   194Рєњ\n   195РєњSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   196Рєњ\n   197РєњStep-level `agent_command` and `agent_args` override workflow-level defaults. The\n   198Рєњresolution order is: step-level > workflow-level block > `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` env\n   199Рєњvar > default `claude`.\n   200Рєњ\n   201Рєњ## Host Workflow Example\n   202Рєњ\n   203РєњA three-phase `host.cloche` with separate `list-tasks`, `main`, and `finalize`\n   204Рєњworkflows:\n   205Рєњ\n   206Рєњ```\n   207Рєњ# .cloche/host.cloche Рђћ runs on the host machine\n   208Рєњ\n   209Рєњworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   210Рєњ  step fetch-tickets {\n   211Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   212Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   213Рєњ  }\n   214Рєњ\n   215Рєњ  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   216Рєњ  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   217Рєњ}\n   218Рєњ\n   219Рєњworkflow \"main\" {\n   220Рєњ  host {\n   221Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   222Рєњ  }\n   223Рєњ\n   224Рєњ  step prepare-prompt {\n   225Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   226Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   227Рєњ  }\n   228Рєњ\n   229Рєњ  step develop {\n   230Рєњ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   231Рєњ    results       = [success, fail]\n   232Рєњ  }\n   233Рєњ\n   234Рєњ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   235Рєњ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   236Рєњ  develop:success        -> done\n   237Рєњ  develop:fail           -> done\n   238Рєњ}\n   239Рєњ\n   240Рєњworkflow \"finalize\" {\n   241Рєњ  step push-for-review {\n   242Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   243Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   244Рєњ  }\n   245Рєњ\n   246Рєњ  push-for-review:success -> done\n   247Рєњ  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   248Рєњ}\n   249Рєњ```\n   250Рєњ\n   251РєњThe daemon runs `list-tasks` to discover work (output is JSONL), picks an open task,\n   252Рєњruns `main` with `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` set, then runs `finalize` regardless of outcome.\n   253РєњThe `list-tasks` script writes one JSON object per line to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`.\n   254РєњThe `main` workflow receives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket.\n   255РєњThe `finalize` workflow decides what to do based on the outcome (available via\n   256Рєњ`CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars).\n   257Рєњ\n   258Рєњ## Execution Model\n   259Рєњ\n   260Рєњ**Container workflows** are parsed and executed by `cloche-agent` inside a Docker\n   261Рєњcontainer. The agent walks the graph: execute current step, read its result, follow the\n   262Рєњwiring to the next step. This continues until a terminal (`done` or `abort`) is reached.\n   263РєњAll steps run inside the same container. File state accumulates naturally across steps.\n   264Рєњ\n   265Рєњ**Host workflows** are parsed and executed by the daemon on the host machine. A single\n   266Рєњ`host.cloche` file may contain multiple named workflows; the daemon orchestrates them\n   267Рєњin three phases (list-tasks Рєњ main Рєњ finalize). Script steps run via `sh -c` with the\n   268Рєњworking directory set to the **main git worktree** (i.e. the main branch checkout), even\n   269Рєњif the project directory is a linked worktree on a different branch. This ensures\n   270Рєњhost-workflow scripts from main are used for all runs. Workflow steps dispatch container\n   271Рєњruns via the daemon's standard run pipeline. Environment variables (`CLOCHE_TASK_ID`,\n   272Рєњ`CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR`, etc.) are injected into each step; `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` still\n   273Рєњpoints to the actual project directory.\n   274Рєњ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01R9B5ZLwaA81q4buXwXBtpB","session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"502bb20b-c0f1-4b68-a057-e98bd78e213d"}
