[2026-03-13T17:46:46Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F9mk5X1sKY6gnA6NYSCcWk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Рєњpackage main\n     2Рєњ\n     3Рєњimport (\n     4Рєњ\t\"fmt\"\n     5Рєњ\t\"os\"\n     6Рєњ)\n     7Рєњ\n     8Рєњ// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n     9Рєњ// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\n    10Рєњvar subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n    11Рєњ\t\"init\": `cloche init Рђћ Initialize a Cloche project\n    12Рєњ\n    13РєњCreates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\n    14Рєњprompt templates, and configuration files.\n    15Рєњ\n    16РєњUsage:\n    17Рєњ  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n    18Рєњ\n    19РєњFlags:\n    20Рєњ  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n    21Рєњ  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n    22Рєњ\n    23РєњWhat it creates:\n    24Рєњ  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n    25Рєњ  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n    26Рєњ  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n    27Рєњ  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n    28Рєњ  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n    29Рєњ  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n    30Рєњ  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n    31Рєњ  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n    32Рєњ  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n    33Рєњ\n    34РєњExisting files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\n    35Рєњmissing files without losing customizations.\n    36Рєњ\n    37РєњExamples:\n    38Рєњ  cloche init\n    39Рєњ  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n    40Рєњ`,\n    41Рєњ\n    42Рєњ\t\"health\": `cloche health Рђћ Show project health summary\n    43Рєњ\n    44РєњQueries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\n    45Рєњand their pass/fail test counts.\n    46Рєњ\n    47РєњUsage:\n    48Рєњ  cloche health\n    49Рєњ\n    50РєњEnvironment:\n    51Рєњ  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n    52Рєњ\n    53РєњExamples:\n    54Рєњ  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n    55Рєњ  cloche health\n    56Рєњ`,\n    57Рєњ\n    58Рєњ\t\"run\": `cloche run Рђћ Launch a workflow run\n    59Рєњ\n    60РєњStarts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\n    61Рєњimage, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n    62Рєњ\n    63РєњUsage:\n    64Рєњ  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n    65Рєњ  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n    66Рєњ\n    67РєњFlags:\n    68Рєњ  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n    69Рєњ                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n    70Рєњ  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n    71Рєњ  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n    72Рєњ  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n    73Рєњ  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n    74Рєњ                       Useful for debugging.\n    75Рєњ\n    76РєњThe command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\n    77Рєњpoll, and stop.\n    78Рєњ\n    79РєњExamples:\n    80Рєњ  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n    81Рєњ  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n    82Рєњ  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n    83Рєњ`,\n    84Рєњ\n    85Рєњ\t\"status\": `cloche status Рђћ Check run status\n    86Рєњ\n    87РєњShows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\n    88Рєњand the result of each completed step.\n    89Рєњ\n    90РєњUsage:\n    91Рєњ  cloche status <run-id>\n    92Рєњ\n    93РєњArguments:\n    94Рєњ  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n    95Рєњ\n    96РєњOutput fields:\n    97Рєњ  Run         Run identifier\n    98Рєњ  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n    99Рєњ  Workflow    Workflow name\n   100Рєњ  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n   101Рєњ  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n   102Рєњ  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n   103Рєњ  Error       Error message (if failed)\n   104Рєњ  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n   105Рєњ  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n   106Рєњ\n   107РєњExamples:\n   108Рєњ  cloche status abc123\n   109Рєњ`,\n   110Рєњ\n   111Рєњ\t\"logs\": `cloche logs Рђћ Show logs for a run\n   112Рєњ\n   113РєњStreams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   114Рєњstep name and log type, and can follow live output.\n   115Рєњ\n   116РєњUsage:\n   117Рєњ  cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n   118Рєњ\n   119РєњArguments:\n   120Рєњ  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   121Рєњ\n   122РєњFlags:\n   123Рєњ  --step <name>                  Show logs only for the named step.\n   124Рєњ  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n   125Рєњ                                   full    Рђћ complete unfiltered output\n   126Рєњ                                   script  Рђћ script/command output only\n   127Рєњ                                   llm     Рђћ LLM interaction logs only\n   128Рєњ  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n   129Рєњ                                 run completes or is stopped).\n   130Рєњ\n   131РєњExamples:\n   132Рєњ  cloche logs abc123\n   133Рєњ  cloche logs abc123 --step implement --type llm\n   134Рєњ  cloche logs abc123 -f\n   135Рєњ  cloche logs abc123 --step test --type script\n   136Рєњ`,\n   137Рєњ\n   138Рєњ\t\"poll\": `cloche poll Рђћ Wait for a run to finish\n   139Рєњ\n   140РєњPolls the daemon every 2 seconds and prints step-level progress until the\n   141Рєњrun reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n   142Рєњ\n   143РєњUsage:\n   144Рєњ  cloche poll <run-id>\n   145Рєњ\n   146РєњArguments:\n   147Рєњ  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   148Рєњ\n   149РєњExit codes:\n   150Рєњ  0    Run succeeded.\n   151Рєњ  1    Run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n   152Рєњ\n   153РєњExamples:\n   154Рєњ  cloche poll abc123\n   155Рєњ  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n   156Рєњ`,\n   157Рєњ\n   158Рєњ\t\"list\": `cloche list Рђћ List workflow runs\n   159Рєњ\n   160РєњShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\n   161Рєњwith --all.\n   162Рєњ\n   163РєњUsage:\n   164Рєњ  cloche list [--all]\n   165Рєњ\n   166РєњFlags:\n   167Рєњ  --all    Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n   168Рєњ\n   169РєњOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\n   170Рєњtitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n   171Рєњ\n   172РєњExamples:\n   173Рєњ  cloche list\n   174Рєњ  cloche list --all\n   175Рєњ`,\n   176Рєњ\n   177Рєњ\t\"stop\": `cloche stop Рђћ Stop a running workflow\n   178Рєњ\n   179РєњSends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\n   180Рєњand the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n   181Рєњ\n   182РєњUsage:\n   183Рєњ  cloche stop <run-id>\n   184Рєњ\n   185РєњArguments:\n   186Рєњ  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   187Рєњ\n   188РєњExamples:\n   189Рєњ  cloche stop abc123\n   190Рєњ`,\n   191Рєњ\n   192Рєњ\t\"delete\": `cloche delete Рђћ Delete a retained container\n   193Рєњ\n   194РєњRemoves a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\n   195РєњAccepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n   196Рєњ\n   197РєњUsage:\n   198Рєњ  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   199Рєњ\n   200РєњArguments:\n   201Рєњ  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n   202Рєњ\n   203РєњExamples:\n   204Рєњ  cloche delete abc123\n   205Рєњ`,\n   206Рєњ\n   207Рєњ\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks Рђћ Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   208Рєњ\n   209РєњQueries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\n   210Рєњtasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n   211Рєњ\n   212РєњUsage:\n   213Рєњ  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   214Рєњ\n   215РєњFlags:\n   216Рєњ  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n   217Рєњ                     directory basename).\n   218Рєњ\n   219РєњEnvironment:\n   220Рєњ  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n   221Рєњ\n   222РєњOutput columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n   223Рєњ\n   224РєњExamples:\n   225Рєњ  cloche tasks\n   226Рєњ  cloche tasks --project my-app\n   227Рєњ`,\n   228Рєњ\n   229Рєњ\t\"loop\": `cloche loop Рђћ Manage the orchestration loop\n   230Рєњ\n   231РєњStarts or stops the daemon's orchestration loop, which automatically\n   232Рєњpicks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n   233Рєњ\n   234РєњUsage:\n   235Рєњ  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n   236Рєњ  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n   237Рєњ\n   238РєњFlags:\n   239Рєњ  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n   240Рєњ               .cloche/config.toml).\n   241Рєњ\n   242РєњExamples:\n   243Рєњ  cloche loop\n   244Рєњ  cloche loop --max 3\n   245Рєњ  cloche loop stop\n   246Рєњ`,\n   247Рєњ\n   248Рєњ\t\"get\": `cloche get Рђћ Get a value from the run context store\n   249Рєњ\n   250РєњReads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\n   251Рєњworkflow scripts and steps.\n   252Рєњ\n   253РєњUsage:\n   254Рєњ  cloche get <key>\n   255Рєњ\n   256РєњArguments:\n   257Рєњ  <key>    The context key to read.\n   258Рєњ\n   259РєњEnvironment:\n   260Рєњ  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   261Рєњ  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   262Рєњ\n   263РєњExit codes:\n   264Рєњ  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n   265Рєњ  1    Key not found or error.\n   266Рєњ\n   267РєњExamples:\n   268Рєњ  cloche get branch\n   269Рєњ  cloche get task_id\n   270Рєњ`,\n   271Рєњ\n   272Рєњ\t\"set\": `cloche set Рђћ Set a value in the run context store\n   273Рєњ\n   274РєњWrites a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\n   275Рєњvalue to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n   276Рєњ\n   277РєњUsage:\n   278Рєњ  cloche set <key> <value>\n   279Рєњ  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n   280Рєњ\n   281РєњArguments:\n   282Рєњ  <key>      The context key to write.\n   283Рєњ  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n   284Рєњ\n   285РєњEnvironment:\n   286Рєњ  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n   287Рєњ  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n   288Рєњ\n   289РєњExamples:\n   290Рєњ  cloche set branch feature-auth\n   291Рєњ  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n   292Рєњ`,\n   293Рєњ\n   294Рєњ\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown Рђћ Shut down the daemon\n   295Рєњ\n   296РєњSends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. All running workflows are\n   297Рєњstopped and the daemon process exits.\n   298Рєњ\n   299РєњUsage:\n   300Рєњ  cloche shutdown\n   301Рєњ\n   302РєњExamples:\n   303Рєњ  cloche shutdown\n   304Рєњ`,\n   305Рєњ}\n   306Рєњ\n   307Рєњ// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n   308Рєњ// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\n   309Рєњfunc printHelp(args []string) bool {\n   310Рєњ\tif len(args) == 0 {\n   311Рєњ\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   312Рєњ\t\treturn true\n   313Рєњ\t}\n   314Рєњ\n   315Рєњ\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n   316Рєњ\tcmd := args[0]\n   317Рєњ\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   318Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   319Рєњ\t\treturn true\n   320Рєњ\t}\n   321Рєњ\n   322Рєњ\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n   323Рєњ\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n   324Рєњ\treturn true\n   325Рєњ}\n   326Рєњ\n   327Рєњ// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\n   328Рєњfunc hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n   329Рєњ\tfor _, arg := range args {\n   330Рєњ\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n   331Рєњ\t\t\treturn true\n   332Рєњ\t\t}\n   333Рєњ\t}\n   334Рєњ\treturn false\n   335Рєњ}\n   336Рєњ\n   337Рєњ// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\n   338Рєњfunc printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n   339Рєњ\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n   340Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n   341Рєњ\t} else {\n   342Рєњ\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n   343Рєњ\t}\n   344Рєњ}\n   345Рєњ\n   346Рєњfunc printTopLevelHelp() {\n   347Рєњ\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche Рђћ Grow-code high quality applications\n   348Рєњ\n   349РєњCloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\n   350Рєњfor linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n   351Рєњ\n   352РєњUsage:\n   353Рєњ  cloche <command> [args]\n   354Рєњ  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n   355Рєњ  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n   356Рєњ\n   357РєњProject Setup:\n   358Рєњ  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n   359Рєњ  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n   360Рєњ\n   361РєњWorkflow Runs:\n   362Рєњ  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n   363Рєњ  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n   364Рєњ  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n   365Рєњ  poll       Wait for a run to finish (blocks until terminal state)\n   366Рєњ  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n   367Рєњ  stop       Stop a running workflow\n   368Рєњ  delete     Delete a retained container\n   369Рєњ\n   370РєњOrchestration:\n   371Рєњ  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n   372Рєњ  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n   373Рєњ\n   374РєњContext Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n   375Рєњ  get        Get a value from the run context store\n   376Рєњ  set        Set a value in the run context store\n   377Рєњ\n   378РєњDaemon:\n   379Рєњ  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n   380Рєњ\n   381РєњEnvironment Variables:\n   382Рєњ  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n   383Рєњ  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n   384Рєњ  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n   385Рєњ  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n   386Рєњ\n   387РєњExamples:\n   388Рєњ  cloche init\n   389Рєњ  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n   390Рєњ  cloche status abc123\n   391Рєњ  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n   392Рєњ  cloche list\n   393Рєњ  cloche loop --max 2\n   394Рєњ`)\n   395Рєњ}\n   396Рєњ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"824f09ed-450b-4e33-88c5-1585f66e5eba","uuid":"40982313-8331-4416-bff3-e064e46c5662","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go","content":"package main\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"os\"\n)\n\n// subcommandHelp maps each subcommand to its detailed help text.\n// Help text is formatted for LLM consumption: structured, explicit, with examples.\nvar subcommandHelp = map[string]string{\n\t\"init\": `cloche init Рђћ Initialize a Cloche project\n\nCreates the .cloche/ directory with a workflow definition, Dockerfile,\nprompt templates, and configuration files.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n\nFlags:\n  --workflow <name>       Name for the workflow file (default: \"develop\")\n  --base-image <image>    Base Docker image for the Dockerfile (default: \"cloche-base:latest\")\n\nWhat it creates:\n  .cloche/<name>.cloche           Workflow definition\n  .cloche/host.cloche             Host orchestration workflow\n  .cloche/Dockerfile              Container image definition\n  .cloche/config.toml             Project configuration\n  .cloche/prompts/implement.md    Prompt for the implement step\n  .cloche/prompts/fix.md          Prompt for the fix step\n  .cloche/prompts/update-docs.md  Prompt for the update-docs step\n  .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh  Prompt generation script\n  .cloche/version                 Schema version marker\n\nExisting files are never overwritten. Run this command again safely to add\nmissing files without losing customizations.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche init\n  cloche init --workflow build --base-image python:3.12\n`,\n\n\t\"health\": `cloche health Рђћ Show project health summary\n\nQueries the daemon's HTTP API for a summary of all registered projects\nand their pass/fail test counts.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche health\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (e.g. \"localhost:8080\"). Required.\n\nExamples:\n  export CLOCHE_HTTP=localhost:8080\n  cloche health\n`,\n\n\t\"run\": `cloche run Рђћ Launch a workflow run\n\nStarts a new container workflow run. The daemon builds/pulls the container\nimage, copies the project into it, and executes the workflow steps.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n  cloche run <name>              (shorthand: bare positional workflow name)\n\nFlags:\n  --workflow <name>    Name of the workflow to run (required). Must match a\n                       .cloche/<name>.cloche file in the project.\n  --prompt \"...\"       Prompt text passed to agent steps. Also available as\n  -p \"...\"             the short form.\n  --title \"...\"        Human-readable title for the run (shown in status/list).\n  --keep-container     Do not remove the container after the run completes.\n                       Useful for debugging.\n\nThe command prints the run ID on success. Use that ID with status, logs,\npoll, and stop.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add a /health endpoint\"\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix the broken CSV parser\" --title \"CSV fix\"\n  cloche run --workflow build --keep-container\n`,\n\n\t\"status\": `cloche status Рђћ Check run status\n\nShows the current state of a workflow run including its type, active step,\nand the result of each completed step.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche status <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier returned by \"cloche run\".\n\nOutput fields:\n  Run         Run identifier\n  Title       Human-readable title (if set)\n  Workflow    Workflow name\n  Type        \"host\" or \"container\"\n  State       Current state (e.g. running, succeeded, failed, cancelled)\n  Container   Truncated container ID (container runs only)\n  Error       Error message (if failed)\n  Active      Name of the currently executing step\n  Steps       List of completed steps with results and timestamps\n\nExamples:\n  cloche status abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"logs\": `cloche logs Рђћ Show logs for a run\n\nStreams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\nstep name and log type, and can follow live output.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nFlags:\n  --step <name>                  Show logs only for the named step.\n  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n                                   full    Рђћ complete unfiltered output\n                                   script  Рђћ script/command output only\n                                   llm     Рђћ LLM interaction logs only\n  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n                                 run completes or is stopped).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche logs abc123\n  cloche logs abc123 --step implement --type llm\n  cloche logs abc123 -f\n  cloche logs abc123 --step test --type script\n`,\n\n\t\"poll\": `cloche poll Рђћ Wait for a run to finish\n\nPolls the daemon every 2 seconds and prints step-level progress until the\nrun reaches a terminal state (succeeded, failed, or cancelled).\n\nUsage:\n  cloche poll <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nExit codes:\n  0    Run succeeded.\n  1    Run failed, was cancelled, or the container died.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche poll abc123\n  cloche run develop -p \"Fix bug\" && cloche poll \"$(cloche run develop -p 'Fix bug')\"\n`,\n\n\t\"list\": `cloche list Рђћ List workflow runs\n\nShows all runs for the current project, or all runs across all projects\nwith --all.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche list [--all]\n\nFlags:\n  --all    Show runs from all projects (default: current project only).\n\nOutput columns: run ID, workflow name, state, type (host/container),\ntitle, container ID, and error message (if any).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche list\n  cloche list --all\n`,\n\n\t\"stop\": `cloche stop Рђћ Stop a running workflow\n\nSends a stop signal to a running workflow. The container is terminated\nand the run state transitions to \"cancelled\".\n\nUsage:\n  cloche stop <run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche stop abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"delete\": `cloche delete Рђћ Delete a retained container\n\nRemoves a container that was kept after a run (via --keep-container).\nAccepts either a container ID or a run ID.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n\nArguments:\n  <container-or-run-id>    Container ID or run ID to delete.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche delete abc123\n`,\n\n\t\"tasks\": `cloche tasks Рђћ Show task pipeline and assignment state\n\nQueries the daemon's HTTP API for the current task list, showing which\ntasks are open, assigned, or completed.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n\nFlags:\n  --project <dir>    Project directory name to query (default: current\n                     directory basename).\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_HTTP    Daemon HTTP address (default: \"localhost:8080\").\n\nOutput columns: ID, STATUS, ASSIGNED, RUN, TITLE\n\nExamples:\n  cloche tasks\n  cloche tasks --project my-app\n`,\n\n\t\"loop\": `cloche loop Рђћ Manage the orchestration loop\n\nStarts or stops the daemon's orchestration loop, which automatically\npicks up and runs tasks from the task pipeline.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche loop [--max <n>]     Start the orchestration loop\n  cloche loop stop            Stop the orchestration loop\n\nFlags:\n  --max <n>    Maximum number of concurrent runs (default: value from\n               .cloche/config.toml).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche loop\n  cloche loop --max 3\n  cloche loop stop\n`,\n\n\t\"get\": `cloche get Рђћ Get a value from the run context store\n\nReads a key from the run's context.json file. Intended for use inside\nworkflow scripts and steps.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche get <key>\n\nArguments:\n  <key>    The context key to read.\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n\nExit codes:\n  0    Key exists; value printed to stdout.\n  1    Key not found or error.\n\nExamples:\n  cloche get branch\n  cloche get task_id\n`,\n\n\t\"set\": `cloche set Рђћ Set a value in the run context store\n\nWrites a key-value pair to the run's context.json file. Use \"-\" as the\nvalue to read from stdin (useful for multi-line content).\n\nUsage:\n  cloche set <key> <value>\n  cloche set <key> -          (read value from stdin)\n\nArguments:\n  <key>      The context key to write.\n  <value>    The value to store, or \"-\" to read from stdin.\n\nEnvironment:\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run identifier (required).\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory (default: current directory).\n\nExamples:\n  cloche set branch feature-auth\n  echo \"multi-line content\" | cloche set notes -\n`,\n\n\t\"shutdown\": `cloche shutdown Рђћ Shut down the daemon\n\nSends a shutdown signal to the Cloche daemon. All running workflows are\nstopped and the daemon process exits.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche shutdown\n\nExamples:\n  cloche shutdown\n`,\n}\n\n// printHelp prints the top-level help or subcommand-specific help.\n// Returns true if help was printed (caller should exit).\nfunc printHelp(args []string) bool {\n\tif len(args) == 0 {\n\t\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\n\t// \"cloche help <subcommand>\"\n\tcmd := args[0]\n\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n\t\treturn true\n\t}\n\n\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"unknown command: %s\\n\\n\", cmd)\n\tprintTopLevelHelp()\n\treturn true\n}\n\n// hasHelpFlag returns true if the args contain --help or -h.\nfunc hasHelpFlag(args []string) bool {\n\tfor _, arg := range args {\n\t\tif arg == \"--help\" || arg == \"-h\" {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n\n// printSubcommandHelp prints help for a subcommand and exits.\nfunc printSubcommandHelp(cmd string) {\n\tif text, ok := subcommandHelp[cmd]; ok {\n\t\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, text)\n\t} else {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"no help available for %q\\n\", cmd)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc printTopLevelHelp() {\n\tfmt.Fprint(os.Stderr, `cloche Рђћ Grow-code high quality applications\n\nCloche provides containerized environments for coding agents, a workflow DSL\nfor linking agentic and script-driven tasks, and validated code pipelines.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche <command> [args]\n  cloche help <command>       Show detailed help for a command\n  cloche <command> --help     Same as above\n\nProject Setup:\n  init       Initialize a Cloche project (.cloche/ directory and templates)\n  health     Show project health summary (pass/fail counts)\n\nWorkflow Runs:\n  run        Launch a workflow run in a container\n  status     Check run status (state, steps, errors)\n  logs       Show or stream logs for a run\n  poll       Wait for a run to finish (blocks until terminal state)\n  list       List runs for current project (or all projects)\n  stop       Stop a running workflow\n  delete     Delete a retained container\n\nOrchestration:\n  tasks      Show task pipeline and assignment state\n  loop       Start or stop the orchestration loop\n\nContext Store (for use inside workflow steps):\n  get        Get a value from the run context store\n  set        Set a value in the run context store\n\nDaemon:\n  shutdown   Shut down the Cloche daemon\n\nEnvironment Variables:\n  CLOCHE_ADDR          Daemon gRPC address (default: unix:///tmp/cloche.sock)\n  CLOCHE_HTTP          Daemon HTTP address (for health/tasks commands)\n  CLOCHE_RUN_ID        Run ID for get/set commands (set automatically in steps)\n  CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR   Project directory override for get/set commands\n\nExamples:\n  cloche init\n  cloche run --workflow develop --prompt \"Add user authentication\"\n  cloche status abc123\n  cloche logs abc123 --follow\n  cloche list\n  cloche loop --max 2\n`)\n}\n","numLines":396,"startLine":1,"totalLines":396}}}
