[2026-03-13T17:47:31Z] [llm] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01TqSNrnNPq4x1KB81X59st4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0169p5ShXrn8NrNKyVyKx2rV","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1181,"cache_read_input_tokens":42755,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1181},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2090add2-0fe6-4270-9f3b-b52deb6bac91","uuid":"0339450a-f95f-43b6-9d33-c1009404ef9f"}
[2026-03-13T17:47:31Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0169p5ShXrn8NrNKyVyKx2rV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1Рєњ# Cloche Usage\n     2Рєњ\n     3РєњCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\n     4Рєњworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\n     5Рєњcontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\n     6Рєњresults to a git branch.\n     7Рєњ\n     8Рєњ## Core Concepts\n     9Рєњ\n    10Рєњ- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n    11Рєњ- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n    12Рєњ- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n    13Рєњ- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n    14Рєњ- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n    15Рєњ\n    16Рєњ## Workflow DSL\n    17Рєњ\n    18РєњWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\n    19Рєњdeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\n    20Рєњno orphans, entry point exists).\n    21Рєњ\n    22Рєњ### Minimal Example\n    23Рєњ\n    24Рєњ```\n    25Рєњworkflow \"develop\" {\n    26Рєњ  step implement {\n    27Рєњ    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    28Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n    29Рєњ  }\n    30Рєњ\n    31Рєњ  step test {\n    32Рєњ    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    33Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n    34Рєњ  }\n    35Рєњ\n    36Рєњ  implement:success -> test\n    37Рєњ  implement:fail -> abort\n    38Рєњ  test:success -> done\n    39Рєњ  test:fail -> abort\n    40Рєњ}\n    41Рєњ```\n    42Рєњ\n    43Рєњ### Step Configuration\n    44Рєњ\n    45Рєњ| Key | Type | Description |\n    46Рєњ|-----|------|-------------|\n    47Рєњ| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n    48Рєњ| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n    49Рєњ| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n    50Рєњ| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n    51Рєњ| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n    52Рєњ| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n    53Рєњ| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n    54Рєњ| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n    55Рєњ| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n    56Рєњ| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n    57Рєњ\n    58РєњA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n    59Рєњ\n    60Рєњ### The `file()` Function\n    61Рєњ\n    62Рєњ`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n    63Рєњ(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\n    64Рєњtemplates:\n    65Рєњ\n    66Рєњ```\n    67Рєњprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    68Рєњ```\n    69Рєњ\n    70Рєњ### The `container {}` Block\n    71Рєњ\n    72РєњCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n    73Рєњ\n    74Рєњ**Step level** Рђћ per-step container config:\n    75Рєњ```\n    76Рєњstep code {\n    77Рєњ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    78Рєњ  container {\n    79Рєњ    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    80Рєњ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    81Рєњ    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n    82Рєњ  }\n    83Рєњ  results = [success, fail]\n    84Рєњ}\n    85Рєњ```\n    86Рєњ\n    87Рєњ**Workflow level** Рђћ defaults for all steps:\n    88Рєњ```\n    89Рєњworkflow \"develop\" {\n    90Рєњ  container {\n    91Рєњ    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    92Рєњ    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    93Рєњ    memory        = \"4g\"\n    94Рєњ  }\n    95Рєњ  ...\n    96Рєњ}\n    97Рєњ```\n    98Рєњ\n    99РєњSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n   100Рєњ\n   101Рєњ### The `host {}` Block\n   102Рєњ\n   103РєњCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\n   104Рєњwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n   105Рєњ\n   106Рєњ```\n   107Рєњworkflow \"main\" {\n   108Рєњ  host {\n   109Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   110Рєњ  }\n   111Рєњ  ...\n   112Рєњ}\n   113Рєњ```\n   114Рєњ\n   115РєњSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n   116Рєњ`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n   117Рєњ\n   118Рєњ### Wiring Syntax\n   119Рєњ\n   120РєњConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n   121Рєњ\n   122Рєњ```\n   123Рєњimplement:success -> test\n   124Рєњimplement:fail -> abort\n   125Рєњtest:success -> done\n   126Рєњtest:fail -> fix\n   127Рєњ```\n   128Рєњ\n   129Рєњ### Wire Output Mappings\n   130Рєњ\n   131РєњExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n   132Рєњ\n   133Рєњ```\n   134Рєњstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n   135Рєњ```\n   136Рєњ\n   137РєњPath expressions:\n   138Рєњ\n   139Рєњ| Expression | Meaning |\n   140Рєњ|---|---|\n   141Рєњ| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n   142Рєњ| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n   143Рєњ| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n   144Рєњ| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n   145Рєњ| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n   146Рєњ\n   147РєњIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\n   148Рєњtext, only bare `output` works.\n   149Рєњ\n   150Рєњ### Retry Loops\n   151Рєњ\n   152РєњWire failures back to earlier steps:\n   153Рєњ\n   154Рєњ```\n   155Рєњtest:fail -> fix\n   156Рєњfix:success -> test    // retry the test\n   157Рєњfix:fail -> abort\n   158Рєњ```\n   159Рєњ\n   160РєњUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n   161Рєњ\n   162Рєњ```\n   163Рєњstep fix {\n   164Рєњ  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n   165Рєњ  max_attempts = \"2\"\n   166Рєњ  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   167Рєњ}\n   168Рєњ```\n   169Рєњ\n   170Рєњ### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n   171Рєњ\n   172РєњWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n   173Рєњ\n   174Рєњ```\n   175Рєњtest:success -> lint\n   176Рєњtest:success -> quality\n   177Рєњ```\n   178Рєњ\n   179Рєњ### Collect (Join)\n   180Рєњ\n   181РєњSynchronize parallel branches:\n   182Рєњ\n   183Рєњ```\n   184Рєњcollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   185Рєњcollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   186Рєњ```\n   187Рєњ\n   188Рєњ`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n   189Рєњ\n   190Рєњ### Comments\n   191Рєњ\n   192РєњLine comments with `//`:\n   193Рєњ\n   194Рєњ```\n   195Рєњ// This is a comment\n   196Рєњimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n   197Рєњ```\n   198Рєњ\n   199Рєњ## Result Protocol\n   200Рєњ\n   201РєњSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n   202Рєњ\n   203Рєњ```\n   204РєњCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n   205Рєњ```\n   206Рєњ\n   207РєњFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n   208Рєњ\n   209РєњRules:\n   210Рєњ- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n   211Рєњ- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n   212Рєњ- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n   213Рєњ- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n   214Рєњ- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n   215Рєњ\n   216Рєњ## Prompt Assembly\n   217Рєњ\n   218РєњWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n   219Рєњ\n   220Рєњ1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n   221Рєњ2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n   222Рєњ3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n   223Рєњ4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n   224Рєњ\n   225РєњThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n   226Рєњ\n   227Рєњ## Agent Command Resolution\n   228Рєњ\n   229РєњPriority (highest to lowest):\n   230Рєњ1. Step-level `agent_command`\n   231Рєњ2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n   232Рєњ3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n   233Рєњ4. Default: `claude`\n   234Рєњ\n   235Рєњ### Fallback Chains\n   236Рєњ\n   237РєњComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n   238Рєњ\n   239Рєњ```\n   240Рєњagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n   241Рєњ```\n   242Рєњ\n   243Рєњ- **Command not found / failed to start** Рђћ try next command\n   244Рєњ- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** Рђћ try next command\n   245Рєњ- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** Рђћ use that result (no fallback)\n   246Рєњ- **Exit 0** Рђћ use result (no fallback)\n   247Рєњ- **All commands fail to start** Рђћ step returns an error\n   248Рєњ- **Last command crashes without marker** Рђћ step returns `fail`\n   249Рєњ\n   250РєњKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n   251Рєњ\n   252Рєњ### Agent Setup Guides\n   253Рєњ\n   254РєњFor detailed container setup instructions per agent:\n   255Рєњ\n   256Рєњ- [How to set up Claude Code](agent-setup-claude.md) Рђћ session-based auth, no API key needed\n   257Рєњ- [How to set up Codex](agent-setup-codex.md) Рђћ API key configuration\n   258Рєњ\n   259Рєњ## Workflow Locations\n   260Рєњ\n   261Рєњ**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\n   262Рєњvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n   263Рєњ\n   264Рєњ**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\n   265РєњSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\n   266Рєњdispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\n   267Рєњexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\n   268Рєњfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n   269Рєњ\n   270РєњA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\n   271Рєњuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n   272Рєњ\n   273Рєњ| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n   274Рєњ|-------|--------------|---------|\n   275Рєњ| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n   276Рєњ| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n   277Рєњ| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n   278Рєњ\n   279РєњOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\n   280Рєњmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n   281Рєњ\n   282Рєњ### list-tasks Output Format\n   283Рєњ\n   284РєњThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\n   285Рєњobject:\n   286Рєњ\n   287Рєњ| Field | Required | Description |\n   288Рєњ|-------|----------|-------------|\n   289Рєњ| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n   290Рєњ| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n   291Рєњ| `title` | no | Short summary |\n   292Рєњ| `description` | no | Full description |\n   293Рєњ| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n   294Рєњ\n   295РєњThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\n   296Рєњset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\n   297Рєњdeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n   298Рєњ\n   299Рєњ### Host Workflow Example\n   300Рєњ\n   301РєњA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n   302Рєњ\n   303Рєњ```\n   304Рєњworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n   305Рєњ  step fetch-tickets {\n   306Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n   307Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   308Рєњ  }\n   309Рєњ\n   310Рєњ  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n   311Рєњ  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n   312Рєњ}\n   313Рєњ\n   314Рєњworkflow \"main\" {\n   315Рєњ  host {\n   316Рєњ    agent_command = \"claude\"\n   317Рєњ  }\n   318Рєњ\n   319Рєњ  step prepare-prompt {\n   320Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n   321Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   322Рєњ  }\n   323Рєњ\n   324Рєњ  step develop {\n   325Рєњ    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n   326Рєњ    results       = [success, fail]\n   327Рєњ  }\n   328Рєњ\n   329Рєњ  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n   330Рєњ  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n   331Рєњ  develop:success        -> done\n   332Рєњ  develop:fail           -> done\n   333Рєњ}\n   334Рєњ\n   335Рєњworkflow \"finalize\" {\n   336Рєњ  step push-for-review {\n   337Рєњ    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n   338Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   339Рєњ  }\n   340Рєњ\n   341Рєњ  push-for-review:success -> done\n   342Рєњ  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n   343Рєњ}\n   344Рєњ```\n   345Рєњ\n   346РєњThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\n   347Рєњreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\n   348Рєњworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\n   349Рєњwhat cleanup to perform.\n   350Рєњ\n   351Рєњ### Host Step Environment Variables\n   352Рєњ\n   353Рєњ| Variable | Description |\n   354Рєњ|----------|-------------|\n   355Рєњ| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n   356Рєњ| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n   357Рєњ| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n   358Рєњ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   359Рєњ| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n   360Рєњ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   361Рєњ| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n   362Рєњ| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n   363Рєњ\n   364Рєњ### Container Environment Variables\n   365Рєњ\n   366Рєњ| Variable | Description |\n   367Рєњ|----------|-------------|\n   368Рєњ| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n   369Рєњ| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Working directory (set for script steps so `cloche get`/`cloche set` work). |\n   370Рєњ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n   371Рєњ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n   372Рєњ\n   373Рєњ## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n   374Рєњ\n   375Рєњ```\n   376Рєњworkflow \"develop\" {\n   377Рєњ  step implement {\n   378Рєњ    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n   379Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   380Рєњ  }\n   381Рєњ\n   382Рєњ  step test {\n   383Рєњ    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n   384Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   385Рєњ  }\n   386Рєњ\n   387Рєњ  step lint {\n   388Рєњ    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n   389Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   390Рєњ  }\n   391Рєњ\n   392Рєњ  step quality {\n   393Рєњ    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n   394Рєњ    results = [success, fail]\n   395Рєњ  }\n   396Рєњ\n   397Рєњ  step fix {\n   398Рєњ    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n   399Рєњ    max_attempts = \"2\"\n   400Рєњ    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n   401Рєњ  }\n   402Рєњ\n   403Рєњ  implement:success -> test\n   404Рєњ  implement:fail -> abort\n   405Рєњ\n   406Рєњ  test:success -> lint\n   407Рєњ  test:success -> quality\n   408Рєњ  test:fail -> fix\n   409Рєњ\n   410Рєњ  lint:fail -> fix\n   411Рєњ  quality:fail -> fix\n   412Рєњ  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n   413Рєњ\n   414Рєњ  fix:success -> test\n   415Рєњ  fix:fail -> abort\n   416Рєњ  fix:give-up -> abort\n   417Рєњ}\n   418Рєњ```\n   419Рєњ\n   420Рєњ## Container Isolation Model\n   421Рєњ\n   422Рєњ- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n   423Рєњ- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n   424Рєњ- **Auth files**: `~/.claude/` and `~/.claude.json` are copied into each container at `/home/agent/` for Claude Code session reuse. Copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own isolated copy.\n   425Рєњ- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n   426Рєњ- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n   427Рєњ\n   428РєњYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n   429Рєњ\n   430Рєњ## CLI Reference\n   431Рєњ\n   432РєњEvery subcommand supports `--help` (or `-h`) to show detailed usage, flags, and\n   433Рєњexamples. Use `cloche help <command>` for the same output:\n   434Рєњ\n   435Рєњ```\n   436Рєњcloche --help              # top-level overview\n   437Рєњcloche help run            # detailed help for \"run\"\n   438Рєњcloche run --help          # same as above\n   439Рєњ```\n   440Рєњ\n   441Рєњ### `cloche init`\n   442Рєњ\n   443РєњScaffold a new Cloche project.\n   444Рєњ\n   445Рєњ```\n   446Рєњcloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n   447Рєњ```\n   448Рєњ\n   449Рєњ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   450Рєњ|------|---------|-------------|\n   451Рєњ| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   452Рєњ| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n   453Рєњ\n   454РєњCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\n   455Рєњhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n   456Рєњ\n   457Рєњ### `cloche run`\n   458Рєњ\n   459РєњLaunch a workflow run.\n   460Рєњ\n   461Рєњ```\n   462Рєњcloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n   463Рєњ```\n   464Рєњ\n   465Рєњ| Flag | Description |\n   466Рєњ|------|-------------|\n   467Рєњ| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n   468Рєњ| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n   469Рєњ| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n   470Рєњ| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n   471Рєњ\n   472РєњMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\n   473Рєњwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n   474Рєњ\n   475Рєњ### `cloche status`\n   476Рєњ\n   477Рєњ```\n   478Рєњcloche status <run-id>\n   479Рєњ```\n   480Рєњ\n   481РєњShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n   482Рєњ\n   483Рєњ### `cloche list`\n   484Рєњ\n   485Рєњ```\n   486Рєњcloche list [--all]\n   487Рєњ```\n   488Рєњ\n   489РєњLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n   490Рєњ\n   491Рєњ### `cloche logs`\n   492Рєњ\n   493Рєњ```\n   494Рєњcloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   495Рєњ```\n   496Рєњ\n   497Рєњ| Flag | Description |\n   498Рєњ|------|-------------|\n   499Рєњ| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   500Рєњ| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   501Рєњ| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   502Рєњ\n   503РєњWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   504Рєњ\n   505Рєњ### `cloche poll`\n   506Рєњ\n   507Рєњ```\n   508Рєњcloche poll <run-id>\n   509Рєњ```\n   510Рєњ\n   511РєњBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n   512Рєњ\n   513Рєњ### `cloche stop`\n   514Рєњ\n   515Рєњ```\n   516Рєњcloche stop <run-id>\n   517Рєњ```\n   518Рєњ\n   519Рєњ### `cloche delete`\n   520Рєњ\n   521Рєњ```\n   522Рєњcloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n   523Рєњ```\n   524Рєњ\n   525РєњDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n   526Рєњ\n   527Рєњ### `cloche health`\n   528Рєњ\n   529Рєњ```\n   530Рєњcloche health\n   531Рєњ```\n   532Рєњ\n   533РєњShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n   534Рєњ\n   535Рєњ### `cloche get`\n   536Рєњ\n   537Рєњ```\n   538Рєњcloche get <key>\n   539Рєњ```\n   540Рєњ\n   541РєњGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   542Рєњthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   543Рєњthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n   544Рєњ\n   545Рєњ### `cloche set`\n   546Рєњ\n   547Рєњ```\n   548Рєњcloche set <key> <value|->\n   549Рєњ```\n   550Рєњ\n   551РєњSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\n   552Рєњthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\n   553Рєњthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\n   554РєњPass `-` as the value to read from stdin (trailing newlines are trimmed).\n   555Рєњ\n   556Рєњ### `cloche tasks`\n   557Рєњ\n   558Рєњ```\n   559Рєњcloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n   560Рєњ```\n   561Рєњ\n   562РєњShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\n   563Рєњupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\n   564Рєњstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n   565Рєњ\n   566Рєњ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   567Рєњ|------|---------|-------------|\n   568Рєњ| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n   569Рєњ\n   570Рєњ### `cloche loop`\n   571Рєњ\n   572РєњStart or stop the daemon's orchestration loop. The loop automatically picks up\n   573Рєњtasks from the pipeline and runs them.\n   574Рєњ\n   575Рєњ```\n   576Рєњcloche loop [--max <n>]\n   577Рєњcloche loop stop\n   578Рєњ```\n   579Рєњ\n   580Рєњ| Flag | Default | Description |\n   581Рєњ|------|---------|-------------|\n   582Рєњ| `--max <n>` | config value | Maximum concurrent runs. Defaults to the value in `.cloche/config.toml`. |\n   583Рєњ\n   584Рєњ`cloche loop stop` disables the loop. Running tasks are not cancelled.\n   585Рєњ\n   586Рєњ### `cloche shutdown`\n   587Рєњ\n   588Рєњ```\n   589Рєњcloche shutdown\n   590Рєњ```\n   591Рєњ\n   592Рєњ## Project Layout\n   593Рєњ\n   594Рєњ```\n   595Рєњmy-project/\n   596РєњРћюРћђРћђ .cloche/\n   597РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\n   598РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\n   599РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\n   600РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ config.toml           # Project configuration\n   601РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ prompts/              # Prompt templates\n   602РєњРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ implement.md\n   603РєњРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ fix.md\n   604РєњРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ update-docs.md\n   605РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\n   606РєњРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\n   607РєњРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\n   608РєњРћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\n   609РєњРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ prompt.txt        # User prompt\n   610РєњРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\n   611РєњРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ output/\n   612РєњРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ full.log      # Unified log\n   613РєњРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ test.log      # Per-step script output\n   614РєњРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\n   615РєњРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\n   616РєњРћѓ       РћћРћђРћђ history.log       # Step execution log\n   617РєњРћюРћђРћђ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\n   618РєњРћћРћђРћђ .git/\n   619Рєњ```\n   620Рєњ\n   621Рєњ## Daemon Configuration\n   622Рєњ\n   623Рєњ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   624Рєњ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   625Рєњ| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n   626Рєњ| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n   627Рєњ| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n   628Рєњ| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n   629Рєњ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n   630Рєњ| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n   631Рєњ| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n   632Рєњ| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n   633Рєњ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n   634Рєњ| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n   635Рєњ\n   636Рєњ### Client Configuration\n   637Рєњ\n   638Рєњ| Variable | Default | Description |\n   639Рєњ|----------|---------|-------------|\n   640Рєњ| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n   641Рєњ| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n   642Рєњ\n   643Рєњ## Dockerfile Requirements\n   644Рєњ\n   645РєњThe container image must have:\n   646Рєњ- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n   647Рєњ- `git` installed\n   648Рєњ- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n   649Рєњ- `/workspace` as the working directory\n   650Рєњ- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n   651Рєњ\n   652Рєњ## Build Commands\n   653Рєњ\n   654Рєњ```\n   655Рєњmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\n   656Рєњmake test           # Run all tests\n   657Рєњmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\n   658Рєњmake lint           # Run go vet\n   659Рєњmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\n   660Рєњmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\n   661Рєњmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\n   662Рєњmake clean          # Remove bin/\n   663Рєњ```\n   664Рєњ"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2090add2-0fe6-4270-9f3b-b52deb6bac91","uuid":"d5af902a-37a6-416f-a965-5f50a5f800b1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"# Cloche Usage\n\nCloche runs containerized workflows for autonomous coding agents. You define a\nworkflow graph in the `.cloche` DSL, Cloche copies your project into a Docker\ncontainer, runs the workflow steps (agent prompts and shell scripts), and extracts\nresults to a git branch.\n\n## Core Concepts\n\n- **Workflow**: A directed graph of steps connected by named-result wiring.\n- **Step**: A unit of work. Type is inferred: `prompt` = agent step, `run` = script step, `workflow_name` = workflow step (host only).\n- **Result**: A named outcome reported by a step (e.g. `success`, `fail`, `needs-research`). Steps declare their possible results; the engine follows wiring based on the reported result.\n- **Wiring**: Maps `step:result` pairs to the next step. Separate from step definitions.\n- **Terminals**: `done` (success) and `abort` (failure) are built-in terminal targets.\n\n## Workflow DSL\n\nWorkflow files use the `.cloche` extension and live in `.cloche/`. The first step\ndeclared is the entry point. Graphs are validated at parse time (all results wired,\nno orphans, entry point exists).\n\n### Minimal Example\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"make test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n  test:success -> done\n  test:fail -> abort\n}\n```\n\n### Step Configuration\n\n| Key | Type | Description |\n|-----|------|-------------|\n| `prompt` | string or `file(\"path\")` | Prompt template. Makes this an agent step. |\n| `run` | string | Shell command. Makes this a script step. |\n| `workflow_name` | string | Container workflow to dispatch. Makes this a workflow step (host only). |\n| `results` | ident list | Declared result names, e.g. `[success, fail, give-up]`. |\n| `max_attempts` | string | Max retries before automatic `give-up` result, e.g. `\"2\"`. |\n| `timeout` | string | Step timeout as Go duration, e.g. `\"30m\"`, `\"2h\"`. Default: 30m. |\n| `agent_command` | string | Agent binary name(s), comma-separated for fallback chains, e.g. `\"claude,gemini\"`. |\n| `agent_args` | string | Override default agent arguments. |\n| `feedback` | string | Set to `\"true\"` to include `.cloche/output/*.log` content in the prompt. |\n| `prompt_step` | string | For workflow steps: which preceding step's output to use as the prompt. |\n\nA step must have exactly one of `prompt`, `run`, or `workflow_name`.\n\n### The `file()` Function\n\n`file(\"path\")` reads the file at the given path relative to the working directory\n(`/workspace/` in containers) at execution time, not parse time. Use it for prompt\ntemplates:\n\n```\nprompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n```\n\n### The `container {}` Block\n\nCan appear at step level or workflow level. Keys are stored with a `container.` prefix.\n\n**Step level** Рђћ per-step container config:\n```\nstep code {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")\n  container {\n    image         = \"custom-agent:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n    network_allow = [\"docs.python.org\", \"api.example.com\"]\n  }\n  results = [success, fail]\n}\n```\n\n**Workflow level** Рђћ defaults for all steps:\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  container {\n    agent_command = \"gemini\"\n    image         = \"myregistry/myimage:v2\"\n    memory        = \"4g\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `image`, `memory`, `network_allow`, `agent_command`, `agent_args`.\n\n### The `host {}` Block\n\nCan appear at workflow level in host workflows (`.cloche/host.cloche`). Keys are stored\nwith a `host.` prefix. Configures agent defaults for agent steps running on the host.\n\n```\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nSupported keys: `agent_command`, `agent_args`. Step-level `agent_command` and\n`agent_args` config keys override the workflow-level `host {}` defaults.\n\n### Wiring Syntax\n\nConnect steps with `step:result -> next_step`:\n\n```\nimplement:success -> test\nimplement:fail -> abort\ntest:success -> done\ntest:fail -> fix\n```\n\n### Wire Output Mappings\n\nExtract values from a step's JSON output and inject as env vars into the target:\n\n```\nstep-a:success -> step-b [ ENV_VAR = output.field, OTHER = output.list[0].name ]\n```\n\nPath expressions:\n\n| Expression | Meaning |\n|---|---|\n| `output` | Raw output (full string) |\n| `output.key` | JSON object field access |\n| `output[N]` | JSON array index (0-based) |\n| `output.a.b.c` | Deeply nested field access |\n| `output.items[0].name` | Mixed field and index chaining |\n\nIf the output is valid JSON, path expressions navigate the structure. If it's plain\ntext, only bare `output` works.\n\n### Retry Loops\n\nWire failures back to earlier steps:\n\n```\ntest:fail -> fix\nfix:success -> test    // retry the test\nfix:fail -> abort\n```\n\nUse `max_attempts` to cap retries. When exhausted, the step returns `give-up`:\n\n```\nstep fix {\n  prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/fix.md\")\n  max_attempts = \"2\"\n  results = [success, fail, give-up]\n}\n```\n\n### Parallel Branches (Fanout)\n\nWire one result to multiple targets for concurrent execution:\n\n```\ntest:success -> lint\ntest:success -> quality\n```\n\n### Collect (Join)\n\nSynchronize parallel branches:\n\n```\ncollect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\ncollect any(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n```\n\n`all` fires when every condition is met. `any` fires when at least one is.\n\n### Comments\n\nLine comments with `//`:\n\n```\n// This is a comment\nimplement:success -> test  // inline comment\n```\n\n## Result Protocol\n\nSteps report results by printing a marker line to stdout:\n\n```\nCLOCHE_RESULT:<name>\n```\n\nFor example: `CLOCHE_RESULT:success`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:needs-research`, `CLOCHE_RESULT:give-up`.\n\nRules:\n- The **last** `CLOCHE_RESULT:` line wins if multiple are printed.\n- Marker lines are **stripped** from captured output (not passed to logs or downstream steps).\n- The result name must match one of the step's declared `results`.\n- For script steps with no marker: exit 0 = `success`, exit non-zero = `fail`.\n- For agent steps: if exit non-zero with a marker, the marker result is used. If exit non-zero without a marker, falls back to the next agent in the fallback chain (or returns `fail` if last).\n\n## Prompt Assembly\n\nWhen an agent step runs, Cloche assembles a prompt from these sections (joined by blank lines):\n\n1. **Step template**: The step's `prompt` content (inline string or resolved `file(\"path\")`).\n2. **User request**: Content of `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt` (set via `--prompt` flag), prefixed with `## User Request`.\n3. **Validation output** (opt-in): If `feedback = \"true\"`, reads all `.log` files from `.cloche/output/` and includes them prefixed with `## Validation Output`.\n4. **Result selection**: Lists the step's declared results with instructions to print exactly one `CLOCHE_RESULT:<name>` marker.\n\nThe assembled prompt is passed to the agent command via stdin.\n\n## Agent Command Resolution\n\nPriority (highest to lowest):\n1. Step-level `agent_command`\n2. Workflow-level config block (`container { agent_command }` for container workflows, `host { agent_command }` for host workflows)\n3. `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` environment variable\n4. Default: `claude`\n\n### Fallback Chains\n\nComma-separated commands are tried in order:\n\n```\nagent_command = \"claude,gemini,codex\"\n```\n\n- **Command not found / failed to start** Рђћ try next command\n- **Exit non-zero without `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** Рђћ try next command\n- **Exit non-zero with `CLOCHE_RESULT` marker** Рђћ use that result (no fallback)\n- **Exit 0** Рђћ use result (no fallback)\n- **All commands fail to start** Рђћ step returns an error\n- **Last command crashes without marker** Рђћ step returns `fail`\n\nKnown agents (e.g. `claude`) get default arguments (`-p --output-format stream-json --verbose --dangerously-skip-permissions`). Unknown agents receive the prompt on stdin with no flags. Override with `agent_args`.\n\n### Agent Setup Guides\n\nFor detailed container setup instructions per agent:\n\n- [How to set up Claude Code](agent-setup-claude.md) Рђћ session-based auth, no API key needed\n- [How to set up Codex](agent-setup-codex.md) Рђћ API key configuration\n\n## Workflow Locations\n\n**Container workflows** (`.cloche/*.cloche` except `host.cloche`) run inside Docker\nvia `cloche-agent`. Steps may only be `agent` or `script` type.\n\n**Host workflow** (`.cloche/host.cloche`) runs on the host machine as the daemon.\nSteps may be `agent`, `script`, or `workflow` type. The `workflow_name` step type\ndispatches a container workflow run and blocks until it completes. Script steps\nexecute with their working directory set to the main git worktree, so host-workflow\nfixes on main are available to in-flight runs even if they branched earlier.\n\nA single `host.cloche` file may contain **multiple named workflows**. The daemon\nuses up to three workflow phases for orchestration:\n\n| Phase | Workflow name | Purpose |\n|-------|--------------|---------|\n| 1 | `list-tasks` | Discover available work. Output is JSONL (one task per line). |\n| 2 | `main` | Do the work. Receives a task ID via `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` env var. |\n| 3 | `finalize` | Post-main cleanup. Runs on **both** success and failure. |\n\nOnly `main` is required. If `list-tasks` is absent, the daemon uses a single-workflow\nmode. If `finalize` is absent, it is skipped.\n\n### list-tasks Output Format\n\nThe `list-tasks` workflow's final step output is parsed as JSONL. Each line is a JSON\nobject:\n\n| Field | Required | Description |\n|-------|----------|-------------|\n| `id` | yes | Unique task identifier |\n| `status` | yes | One of `open`, `closed`, `in-progress` |\n| `title` | no | Short summary |\n| `description` | no | Full description |\n| `metadata` | no | Arbitrary key-value pairs |\n\nThe daemon picks the first task with status `open`, runs `main` with that task's ID\nset in `CLOCHE_TASK_ID`, then runs `finalize` with the outcome. Tasks are\ndeduplicated within a timeout window to prevent rapid reassignment of the same task.\n\n### Host Workflow Example\n\nA three-phase `host.cloche`:\n\n```\nworkflow \"list-tasks\" {\n  step fetch-tickets {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/ready-tasks.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  fetch-tickets:success -> done\n  fetch-tickets:fail    -> abort\n}\n\nworkflow \"main\" {\n  host {\n    agent_command = \"claude\"\n  }\n\n  step prepare-prompt {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/prepare-prompt.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step develop {\n    workflow_name = \"develop\"\n    results       = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  prepare-prompt:success -> develop\n  prepare-prompt:fail    -> abort\n  develop:success        -> done\n  develop:fail           -> done\n}\n\nworkflow \"finalize\" {\n  step push-for-review {\n    run     = \"bash .cloche/scripts/push-for-review.sh\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  push-for-review:success -> done\n  push-for-review:fail    -> done\n}\n```\n\nThe `list-tasks` script writes JSONL to `$CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT`. The `main` workflow\nreceives the task ID and is responsible for claiming the ticket. The `finalize`\nworkflow receives `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` and `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` env vars to decide\nwhat cleanup to perform.\n\n### Host Step Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Absolute path to the project directory on the host. |\n| `CLOCHE_STEP_OUTPUT` | Path where this step should write its output (for output mappings). |\n| `CLOCHE_PREV_OUTPUT` | Path to the output file from the immediately preceding step. |\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `CLOCHE_TASK_ID` | Task ID assigned by the daemon (set for `main` and `finalize` phases). |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_OUTCOME` | Result of the `main` workflow (`succeeded` or `failed`). Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| `CLOCHE_MAIN_RUN_ID` | Run ID of the completed `main` workflow. Set for `finalize` phase only. |\n| Wire-mapped vars | Any env vars declared in wire output mappings. |\n\n### Container Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` | The run ID for this workflow execution. |\n| `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` | Working directory (set for script steps so `cloche get`/`cloche set` work). |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Passed through from the host if set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_COMMAND` | Overrides the default agent command inside the container. |\n\n## Complete Example: Container Workflow with Parallel Validation\n\n```\nworkflow \"develop\" {\n  step implement {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/implement.md\")\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step test {\n    run = \"bundle exec rake test 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step lint {\n    run = \"bundle exec rubocop 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step quality {\n    run = \"python3 scripts/quality-check.py 2>&1\"\n    results = [success, fail]\n  }\n\n  step fix {\n    prompt = file(\"prompts/fix.md\")\n    max_attempts = \"2\"\n    results = [success, fail, give-up]\n  }\n\n  implement:success -> test\n  implement:fail -> abort\n\n  test:success -> lint\n  test:success -> quality\n  test:fail -> fix\n\n  lint:fail -> fix\n  quality:fail -> fix\n  collect all(lint:success, quality:success) -> done\n\n  fix:success -> test\n  fix:fail -> abort\n  fix:give-up -> abort\n}\n```\n\n## Container Isolation Model\n\n- **Files in**: `docker cp` copies the project into `/workspace/`. No bind mounts. Override files from `.cloche/overrides/` are applied on top. `.git/` is included.\n- **Files out**: On completion, the daemon extracts results via `docker cp` into a git worktree and commits to a `cloche/<run-id>` branch.\n- **Auth files**: `~/.claude/` and `~/.claude.json` are copied into each container at `/home/agent/` for Claude Code session reuse. Copied (not bind-mounted) so each container gets its own isolated copy.\n- **Network**: Containers have network access (needed for API calls).\n- **Cleanup**: Containers are removed after successful runs unless `--keep-container` is set. Failed runs always keep their container.\n\nYour project directory is never modified by the container.\n\n## CLI Reference\n\nEvery subcommand supports `--help` (or `-h`) to show detailed usage, flags, and\nexamples. Use `cloche help <command>` for the same output:\n\n```\ncloche --help              # top-level overview\ncloche help run            # detailed help for \"run\"\ncloche run --help          # same as above\n```\n\n### `cloche init`\n\nScaffold a new Cloche project.\n\n```\ncloche init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <base>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | `develop` | Workflow name. Creates `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--base-image <base>` | `cloche-base:latest` | Base Docker image for the generated Dockerfile. |\n\nCreates `.cloche/` with workflow file, Dockerfile, `config.toml`, prompt templates,\nhost workflow (`host.cloche`), and prompt generation script. Skips existing files.\n\n### `cloche run`\n\nLaunch a workflow run.\n\n```\ncloche run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--workflow <name>` | Workflow name. Resolves to `.cloche/<name>.cloche`. |\n| `--prompt \"...\"`, `-p` | Inline prompt written to `.cloche/<run-id>/prompt.txt`. |\n| `--title \"...\"` | One-line summary for status display. Auto-generated if omitted. |\n| `--keep-container` | Keep container on success (failed runs always keep it). |\n\nMust be run from inside a git repository. The daemon auto-rebuilds the Docker image\nwhen `.cloche/Dockerfile` changes.\n\n### `cloche status`\n\n```\ncloche status <run-id>\n```\n\nShows run title, type (`host`/`container`), state, active steps, and per-step results.\n\n### `cloche list`\n\n```\ncloche list [--all]\n```\n\nLists runs for the current project directory. Pass `--all` to show runs across all projects.\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id>\n```\n\nBlock until the run finishes. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 on success, 1 on failure.\n\n### `cloche stop`\n\n```\ncloche stop <run-id>\n```\n\n### `cloche delete`\n\n```\ncloche delete <container-or-run-id>\n```\n\nDelete a retained Docker container by container ID or run ID.\n\n### `cloche health`\n\n```\ncloche health\n```\n\nShow per-project pass/fail summary. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP`.\n\n### `cloche get`\n\n```\ncloche get <key>\n```\n\nGet a value from the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Exits 1 if the key is not found.\n\n### `cloche set`\n\n```\ncloche set <key> <value|->\n```\n\nSet a value in the run context store (`.cloche/<run-id>/context.json`). Requires\nthe `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` environment variable. Uses `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` if set, otherwise\nthe current working directory. Creates the file and directories if they don't exist.\nPass `-` as the value to read from stdin (trailing newlines are trimmed).\n\n### `cloche tasks`\n\n```\ncloche tasks [--project <dir>]\n```\n\nShow the task pipeline and assignment state for an orchestration loop. Displays\nupcoming/open tasks, which tasks are assigned to which runs, and auto-assignment\nstate. Requires `CLOCHE_HTTP` (talks to the daemon's web API).\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--project <dir>` | current directory name | Project to query tasks for. |\n\n### `cloche loop`\n\nStart or stop the daemon's orchestration loop. The loop automatically picks up\ntasks from the pipeline and runs them.\n\n```\ncloche loop [--max <n>]\ncloche loop stop\n```\n\n| Flag | Default | Description |\n|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max <n>` | config value | Maximum concurrent runs. Defaults to the value in `.cloche/config.toml`. |\n\n`cloche loop stop` disables the loop. Running tasks are not cancelled.\n\n### `cloche shutdown`\n\n```\ncloche shutdown\n```\n\n## Project Layout\n\n```\nmy-project/\nРћюРћђРћђ .cloche/\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ develop.cloche        # Container workflow\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ host.cloche           # Host orchestration workflow\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ Dockerfile            # Container image definition\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ config.toml           # Project configuration\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ prompts/              # Prompt templates\nРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ implement.md\nРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ fix.md\nРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ update-docs.md\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ scripts/              # Host-side scripts\nРћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ overrides/            # Files copied on top of /workspace/\nРћѓ   Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ CLAUDE.md         # Container-specific CLAUDE.md (optional)\nРћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ <run-id>/             # Runtime state (gitignored)\nРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ prompt.txt        # User prompt\nРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ context.json      # Shared key-value store (cloche get/set)\nРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ output/\nРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ full.log      # Unified log\nРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћюРћђРћђ test.log      # Per-step script output\nРћѓ       Рћѓ   РћћРћђРћђ llm-impl.log  # Per-step LLM conversation\nРћѓ       РћюРћђРћђ attempt_count/    # Retry counters for max_attempts\nРћѓ       РћћРћђРћђ history.log       # Step execution log\nРћюРћђРћђ src/                      # Project source (untouched by Cloche)\nРћћРћђРћђ .git/\n```\n\n## Daemon Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_LISTEN` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Listen address |\n| `CLOCHE_DB` | `cloche.db` | SQLite database path |\n| `CLOCHE_RUNTIME` | `docker` | `docker` or `local` (subprocess, for dev only) |\n| `CLOCHE_IMAGE` | `cloche-agent:latest` | Default Docker image |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | _(unset)_ | HTTP address for web dashboard. Not started unless set. |\n| `CLOCHE_AGENT_PATH` | _(auto)_ | Path to `cloche-agent` binary (local runtime) |\n| `CLOCHE_LLM_COMMAND` | _(unset)_ | Command for LLM calls (evolution, merge conflicts) |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | _(unset)_ | Passed into Docker containers |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_MOUNTS` | _(unset)_ | Extra bind mounts (comma-separated `host:container`) |\n| `CLOCHE_EXTRA_ENV` | _(unset)_ | Extra env vars (comma-separated `KEY=VALUE`) |\n\n### Client Configuration\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `CLOCHE_ADDR` | `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock` | Daemon gRPC address |\n| `CLOCHE_HTTP` | `localhost:8080` | Daemon HTTP address |\n\n## Dockerfile Requirements\n\nThe container image must have:\n- `cloche-agent` binary at `/usr/local/bin/cloche-agent`\n- `git` installed\n- An `agent` user (cloche wraps commands with `chown` + `su agent`)\n- `/workspace` as the working directory\n- Your project's build dependencies and the agent binary (e.g. `claude`)\n\n## Build Commands\n\n```\nmake build          # Build all binaries to bin/\nmake test           # Run all tests\nmake test-short     # Run tests (skip slow ones)\nmake lint           # Run go vet\nmake proto          # Regenerate gRPC code from protobuf\nmake docker-build   # Build the cloche-agent Docker image\nmake install        # Build, install to ~/.local/bin/, restart daemon\nmake clean          # Remove bin/\n```\n","numLines":664,"startLine":1,"totalLines":664}}}
